    <h3>Document Ingestion Pipeline & Vector Search</h3>
    <p>
        The platform implements a sophisticated <strong>document ingestion pipeline</strong> that transforms unstructured 
        PDFs into searchable vector embeddings. Documents are uploaded via drag-and-drop, stored in Supabase Storage, 
        and processed through a multi-step pipeline: text extraction, intelligent semantic chunking using LangChain's 
        RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter (900 character chunks with 150 character overlap to maintain context continuity), 
        embedding generation with OpenAI's text-embedding-3-small model (1536 dimensions), and storage in PostgreSQL with 
        the pgvector extension. The vector database uses IVFFlat indexing for O(log n) approximate nearest neighbor search, 
        with cosine similarity scoring to find the most relevant document chunks for each query.
    </p>
