    <h3>RAG Chat & Contextual Q&A</h3>
    <p>
        The <strong>RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) chat</strong> enables users to ask natural language questions 
        and receive contextual answers based on their organization's documentation. The system embeds each query using the 
        same embedding model as ingestion (ensuring consistency), performs a vector similarity search to retrieve the top 6 
        most relevant document chunks (with a configurable similarity threshold of 0.75), constructs a context from retrieved 
        chunks, and uses GPT-4.1-mini to generate answers with specialized prompt engineering. Responses are streamed 
        token-by-token using NDJSON format for immediate user feedback. Each answer includes source attribution, showing 
        which specific documents and chunks informed the response. Conversation history is maintained within sessions, 
        allowing for contextual follow-up questions.
    </p>
