    <h3>Multi-Tenant Architecture & Security</h3>
    <p>
        Built with <strong>enterprise-grade security</strong> and true multi-tenancy using Supabase Row-Level Security (RLS). 
        Every database table has RLS policies that enforce organization-level data isolation at the database layer, ensuring 
        users can only access data belonging to their organization. The platform implements a 4-tier Role-Based Access Control 
        (RBAC) system: Viewer (read-only access), Contributor (can upload docs and generate SOPs), Company Admin (full team 
        management, billing, and user invitations), and Super Admin (platform oversight with access to all organizations, 
        system-wide statistics, and monitoring). Permissions are enforced at three levels: UI (hide features based on role), 
        API (server-side validation in route handlers), and Database (RLS policies with role column checks).
    </p>

