    <h3>AI Implementation & Performance</h3>
    <p>
        The platform's <strong>AI architecture</strong> is optimized for cost and performance. Document embeddings use 
        text-embedding-3-small ($0.02/1M tokens) for cost-effectiveness. RAG chat uses GPT-4.1-mini, which is 10x cheaper 
        than GPT-4 and sufficient for factual Q&A. SOP generation uses full GPT-4.1 for complex reasoning and structured 
        output generation. The vector search SQL function uses PostgreSQL's pgvector extension with the cosine distance 
        operator (<=>), indexed with IVFFlat for O(log n) search performance. Typical latencies: query embedding 50-100ms, 
        vector search 100-200ms, LLM first token 500-800ms, full answer 2-4s. Rate limiting prevents abuse (20 chat 
        queries/min per user), and streaming responses provide immediate user feedback with progressive rendering.
    </p>

