    <h3>Code Quality & Architecture</h3>
    <p>
        The codebase follows <strong>SOLID principles</strong> and clean architecture patterns. Built with TypeScript in 
        strict mode (no implicit `any` allowed), functional programming patterns throughout (no classes), and React Server 
        Components (RSC) first architecture with minimal client-side JavaScript (60% CSR / 40% SSR ratio optimized after 
        thorough analysis). The project uses modular folder structure with clear separation of concerns: server-only utilities 
        in `lib/server/`, UI components in `components/`, internationalized routes in `app/[locale]/`, and database migrations 
        in `supabase/migrations/`. All environment variables are validated with Zod schemas at startup, ensuring fast-fail 
        behavior for misconfigurations. The codebase includes comprehensive JSDoc comments for complex functions and maintains 
        consistent naming conventions throughout.
